Take actual far-field response of the shaddock peel-based aerogel materials into consideration, CST Studio Suite 2019 was used for simulating the RCS of the microwave absorber. According to widely accepted metal back model, the simulation model of the specimens was established as a square (20 × 20 cm2) with dual layers. In detail, the upper set as 1.7 mm signifies the absorbing layer and the bottom set as 1.0 mm is the perfect conductive layer (PEC). The shaddock peel-based aerogel-PEC model plate is placed on the X-O-Y plane, and linear polarized plane electromagnetic waves incident from the positive direction of the Z axis to the negative direction of the Z-axis. Meanwhile, the direction of electric polarization propagation is along the X-axis. With the open boundary conditions setting in all directions, the chosen field monitor frequency was 12 GHz. It is generally accepted that the scattering directions can be determined by theta and phi in spherical coordinates. The RCS values can be described as follows[27]:1σdBm2=10log4πS/λ2|Es/Ei|2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
